17/11/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The defence ministry announced on Wednesday (17 November) that a fourth Bulgarian contingent is ready for deployment in Iraq. 
Officials say 57 members of this 462-strong infantry unit served in the first contingent. 
Recently, the Bulgarian base was moved from Karbala to Al-Diwaniyah, Iraq.
In other news, Bulgaria's two major trade unions -- KT Podkrepa and KNSB -- plan to hold a warning strike in Sofia on Thursday. 
Union leaders said the workers are seeking better wages and benefits. 
(bTV, Dnevnik - 17/11/04; BNT - 16/11/04)
